Summary of Key Lessons Learned 
- Security groups are critical even a small IP change can block SSH or DB access.
 - PHP version and extensions must exactly match PrestaShop requirements.
- Low-memory instances (t2/t3.micro) need swap + careful PHP-FPM tuning. 
- RDS requires explicit inbound rules from EC2. 
- Most errors are configuration related (permissions, paths, security groups, syntax) rather than code bugs. 
- Always enable debug mode early to see real errors instead of generic 500/503 messages. 
